description: For sale: $194,900. Finally, your search is over!!  Nestled in a private, pristine setting, this cabin is equipped with a well, central heat, septic system, bathroom - all of the comforts of home!  Start making memories with your family and friends in the middle of Minnesota Whitetail country!  This property adjoins several thousand acres of State land!!  The Willow River runs through the Western parcel and just beyond that you can tap in to the Soo Line Recreational Trail.  This property has produced many deer over the years and the habitat is second-to-none.

description: Recently sold: $350,000. Privacy and Luxury! A very unique property nestled in the pines South of Grand Rapids with 143 Acres on the Willow River. Custom built home with wonderful stone work inside and out. Spacious and open living room with gorgeous FP and Black Ash ceilings & custom carpet. Raised kitchen w/granite floors. The Master BR loft overlooks the living room and kitchen along with cathedral ceilings letting in tons of natural light. The basement is yours for the finishing with walls up and done in T&G, all it needs are flooring and ceiling. Geo Thermal heat & A/C, Integral Foam Cement foundation. There is a unique solarium that leads you into the 4.5 car garage with half of it heated. Nestled in the pines w/a gorgeous view of the Willow River and valley below. Pristine acreage that has 3 heated deer stands and access to the Soo Line Trail. **There is an Option of purchasing the house with 90Acres of land for $359,900.

description: Recently sold: $170,000. WOW!  Wildlife abounds on 40 private acres with state land on two sides!  This darling 3 bedroom, 2 bath home with main floor laundry could be yours.  You will love the spacious eat-in kitchen with oversized sliding glass doors that lead to a beautiful stamped concrete patio.  Relax and listen to the sounds of nature while taking in the peaceful setting with its wildflowers, lilacs & apple trees.  The large, cute upper bedroom has a lot of natural light plus it has many possibilities as it could be used as an art room, office, rec room or yoga studio, the choice is yours.  Other features include a compliant septic, outdoor wood boiler with backup electric plenum heating, seamless steel siding and a 30' x 60' metal pole building.  This would also be a great hobby farm!
